Date: Fri 29 Mar 2002
From: David Sencer <djud2@mindspring.com>

Comment from Dr. Sencer on the History of the Aventis Smallpox
Vaccine
----------------------------------------------------------------------
In the ProMED-mail post entitled, "Smallpox, diluted vaccine trial (08)
20020329.3841", Mod.CP commented that: "The curious rediscovery of
this additional quantity of smallpox vaccine in Lyon (or where ever) is
unexplained. The lack of detail may reflect some reluctance on the part
of the EU to release this material and to retain an amount for the
protection of the European population."
In fact the [rediscovered vaccine was produced and stored in
Swiftwater, PA, USA. Avantis bought the vaccine production facility
from Connaught Laboratories, who in turn had bought it from another
company (memory fades). I believe it was the preceding producer that
produced the smallpox vaccine.
As a side comment, the Swiftwater operation was originally a US
Government facility. The Public Health Service's legislative authority
allows it to produce vaccines that are not commercially available. The
Swiftwater facility was the producer of yellow fever vaccine until the
end of WWII.
--
David J. Sencer,
Atlanta, GA
<djud@mindspring.com>
[ProMED-mail appreciates these two authoritative statements clarifying
the origin and potency of the rediscovered smallpox vaccine. - Mod.CP
